properties.Title: Special Weather Statement In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: First accumulating snowfall of the season may herald the arrival of November. A low pressure system will approach Ontario from the southwest. This weather system will bring a significant rainfall with it tonight through Thursday with many areas receiving a total of 20 to 40 mm of rain by Thursday evening. As the low passes by Thursday night, rain may change over to snow before tapering off Friday. Snowfall amounts of 2 to 4 cm are possible. There is uncertainty in the track of the low, which will affect how quickly the rain will change over to snow and subsequent snowfall amounts. Some folks may wake up to snow covered grass for the first time this season Friday morning. This event will continue to be monitored. Poor winter driving conditions are possible Thursday night. ### Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to ONstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #ONStorm.
